P, Berendsen HJ. Multi-exponential relaxation analysis with MR imaging and NMR spectroscopy using fat-water systems. <em>Magn Reson Imaging</em>1987; 5: 381–392.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/0730-725X(87)90127-5">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/3695824/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Magn+Reson+Imaging&amp;publication_year=1987&amp;pages=381&amp;doi=10.1016%2F0730-725X%2887%2990127-5&amp;pmid=3695824">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div></div></section></div></section></div><div class="core-collateral" role="dialog" aria-modal="true"><div id="core-collateral-info" data-active-pane="false"><header><h2><i class="icon-info" aria-hidden="true"></i>Information &amp; Authors</h2></header><section id="tab-information" role="tabpanel"><h3>Information</h3><section class="core-self-citation"><h4>Published In</h4><div class="core-journal-presentation">



        
        <div class="cover-image flat d-flex justify-content-center flex-column"><div data-is-viewable="" class="cover-image__image"><a href="/toc/radiographics/29/1" title="Go to RadioGraphics " class="d-block"><img src="/cms/10.1148/radiographics.2009.29.issue-1/asset/14a168ae-9b14-168a-99b1-a168ae99b14a/radiographics.2009.29.issue-1.cover.gif" alt="Go to RadioGraphics " loading="lazy"/></a></div></div>
<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">29</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">1</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Jan 1 2009</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">231</span> - <span property="pageEnd">260</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19168847/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">19168847</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2009.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Jan 1 2009</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.291075123">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=FSE+%3D+fast+spin-echo&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">FSE = fast spin-echo</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=FSF+%3D+fat+signal+fraction&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">FSF = fat signal fraction</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=GRE+%3D+gradient-echo&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">GRE = gradient-echo</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=IDEAL+%3D+iterative+decomposition+and+least-square+estimation&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">IDEAL = iterative decomposition and least-square estimation</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=PRESS+%3D+point-resolved+spectroscopy&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">PRESS = point-resolved spectroscopy</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=STEAM+%3D+stimulated-echo+acquisition+mode&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">STEAM = stimulated-echo acquisition mode</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">Three clinically available MR imaging techniques for the detection and quantification of fat are discussed and illustrated in terms of key concepts and basic physical principles, clinical applications, and advantages and disadvantages.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Fiona Hughes</span> <span property="familyName">Cassidy</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology (F.H.C., T.Y., L.A., R.F.H., M.B., M.S.M., G.H., A.D.C., C.B.S.) and Division of Gastroenterology, Hepatology, and Nutrition, Department of Pediatrics (J.B.S.), University of California at San Diego, 200 W Arbor Dr, San Diego, CA 92103; and Department of Radiology, VA Medical Center, San Diego, Calif (F.H.C., L.A.). Presented as an education exhibit at the 2006 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received May 22, 2007; revision requested April 30, 2008; final revision received August 7; accepted August 14. M.B. received a research grant from GE; M.S.M. is a research consultant with Siemens and Confirma, received research grants from GE and Bayer, and is a stockholder of GE; C.B.S. received research grants from Bayer, GE, and Bracco; all other authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Cassidy/Fiona+Hughes" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Takeshi</span> <span property="familyName">Yokoo</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD, PhD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Department of Radiology (F.H.C., T.Y., L.A., R.F.H., M.B., M.S.M., G.H., A.D.C., C.B.S.) and Division of Gastroenterology, Hepatology, and Nutrition, Department of Pediatrics (J.B.S.), University of California at San Diego, 200 W Arbor Dr, San Diego, CA 92103; and Department of Radiology, VA Medical Center, San Diego, Calif (F.H.C., L.A.). Presented as an education exhibit at the 2006 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received May 22, 2007; revision requested April 30, 2008; final revision received August 7; accepted August 14. M.B. received a research grant from GE; M.S.M. is a research consultant with Siemens and Confirma, received research grants from GE and Bayer, and is a stockholder of GE; C.B.S. received research grants from Bayer, GE, and Bracco; all other authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Yokoo/Takeshi" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con3" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Lejla</span> <span property="familyName">Aganovic</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="